parameters: You said the shipment would be here two hours ago!
I’m running a business, not some trash at a mall food court!
You screw me on my order again, and you can forget about me
catering your next party..! Yes I remember...
What can I do you for?
<At least he takes his job seriously...>
Hi there, um... I was hoping to reserve a table for two.
Yeah yeah sure, can pencil you in two weeks from now. Name?
Three weeks. Keep running your mouth, see what happens.
Alright Alright, I’m sorry! I didn’t mean anything by it.
I just really need a table.
And I need a crate of fresh crab for this week's special!
Life's full of disappointment. Now I have to fish for those
damn bottom feeders at the bay because of a late shipment!
You a cop?! It all comes from the ocean! It’s fresh!
<I’m never getting a reservation here, am I?>
I’ll make a deal with you.
You get me my crab, I give you your table.
Crab fishing? I don’t even have a fishing pole!
The crabs are most active at night, so go to the beach late.
Toss this in the water, the crabs will come to you like
flies on shit. Impossible to mess it up.
It’s what you’ll be eating if you don’t bring me the crab!
Do we have a deal or not?
But I don’t have any other options...>
This better be worth it, man.
You’re lucky I’m trying to get laid.
I’ll set you up really pretty if you come through.
Now get out of here with that!
YES, WHAT?! NO, I SAID I WANTED BEEF, NOT PORK!!
ASK THE BUTCHER FOR A BETTER DEAL!!
<I’m not holding this nasty shit any longer than I have to.
Better head to the beach, fast!>
Head to Vesper Beach after the sun goes down.
I hear they have a shampoo for that! HAHAHA!!
Lighten up, kid - you’ll live longer.
*GASP* Where the hell did you get this!?
I could feed twelve people, easy, with this!
Trade secret. Now about that reservation...
Sure Sure! Just say the day and time, and I’ll hook you up.
I’ll cook something special with this, and the meal's on me!
Perfect. Now if you'll excuse me, I need a shower.
Fresh as a daisy! Now I just gotta send Brenda
a text telling her the where and when...
Done! Disgusting shellfish or not, I’m feelin’ pretty
good about this. A little dinner, maybe a drink or two,
who knows where the evening will take us...
Return to Huolong Hot Pot any evening between 5-8PM.
<Damn! Just look at her! How long
has she been waiting to wear that?>
At least I dressed for the occasion...
Uh... Were we supposed to dress nice for this? My bad.
<My wardrobe really is limited, isn’t it..?>
*Ahem* At least you look nice! Hungry?
I’ll have to look at the menu.
<What the fuck is wrong this time? I feel like
every other time I talk to her she's switched
back to full-on bitch mode again...>
<Relax, the night is young. She’ll come around.>
This the lucky lady? You’re in good hands tonight,
sweetcheeks! Meal is on me, this way!
<You need to do this, just stick with it...>
So, what can I get you two to drink?
Two waters, no lemon. Thank you.
Two cheapskates on ice, got it.
I’ll let you look at the menu. Be right back.
So... The book was a hit with the publisher, huh?
Because I can’t wait to read what you have come up with.
<She’s giving me nothing to work with here.
Um... Hey, the Huolong Haul looks pretty good.
I’m trying to watch what I eat.
If you want to make a hog of yourself, be my guest.
Two waters. Now, what can I get you?
... We’ll have two of the specials.
There’s a spot on my glass.
Really? Can’t see it. Maybe you
need to get your eyes checked.
Excuse us, Chef. My friend isn’t herself tonight.
If you wanted to skip dinner, you could have just said so...
I thought you might like a little wining and dining, given
what we’ve done lately. But if you’d rather skip right to
You said you needed more “material” for your next project.
Why not start taking notes early..?
<You can do this... Just break it off, cleanly...
He deserves better than what you can give him, he...>
This... Us? It’s not going to work...
What are you talking about, Brenda?
Oh please, we both knew what this was from the start!
You help me with my writing, you get your A.
We may have had a little fun, but it didn’t mean anything...
I felt bad for you, following me around like a lost puppy.
You didn’t honestly think that I... That we...
After everything we did together... Just like that?
<If you have to make him hate you, to make it easier for
us both... It's okay. After all, I'm used to being hated...>
\n[1], this would have never worked out. I'm at a different
part of my life than you, on the cusp of success, finally,
and I... I don't have time for someone... Like you.
So that’s how it is, huh?
<Where in the actual fuck is this coming from??
She's just  gonna throw me away like that?>
YOU felt bad FOR ME? Wow, that’s...
I don’t even know what to say to that. You’re serious?
I didn’t realize writing one trash romance novel could
create an ego like this that fast. But then again,
they’ll print just about anything these days...
Oh I’m sorry, ALMOST anything. No one would touch your
bad fanfiction, until I came along!
I’M NOT DONE TALKING! Forget your book, and our deal,
I felt sorry for YOU. I saw an insufferable bitch
that maybe, just MAYBE could have been something more...
That maybe if I got to know her...
Thanks for the grade, I’ll save us both the
headache and not show up to class anymore.
Here you are. Should I get doggy bag for his?
You said this meal was on the house!
Free meal for him, not you.
You got my crab yet, kid?
Well hurry up! Wait til it's dark, toss the
bucket in the water and get me my special!
